{{infobox biodatabase |title = TcoF-DB |logo =[[File:Database.png]] |description = human transcription co-factors and [[transcription factor]] [[Protein-protein interaction|interacting proteins]]. |scope = |organism = |center =[[King Abdullah University of Science and Technology]] |laboratory = Computational Bioscience Research Center |author = Schaefer U, Schmeier S, Bajic VB |citation = Schaefer & al. (2011)<ref name="pmid20965969"/> |released = 2010 |standard = |format = |url = http://cbrc.kaust.edu.sa/tcof/ |download = |webservice = |sql = |sparql = |webapp = |standalone = |license = |versioning = |frequency = |curation = |bookmark = |version= }}The '''Dragon Database for Human Transcription Co-Factors and Transcription Factor Interacting Proteins''' ('''TcoF-DB''') is a database that facilitates the exploration of proteins involved in the regulation of [[transcription (genetics)|transcription]] in humans by binding to regulatory DNA regions ([[transcription factors]]) and proteins involved in the regulation of transcription in humans by [[Protein–protein interaction|interacting]] with transcription factors and not binding to regulatory DNA regions ([[Transcription coregulator|transcription co-factors]]).<ref name="pmid20965969">{{cite journal |vauthors=Schaefer U, Schmeier S, Bajic VB |date=Jan 2011|title=TcoF-DB: dragon database for human transcription co-factors and transcription factor interacting proteins|journal = Nucleic Acids Res.|volume=39|issue=Database issue|pages=D106-10|publisher= | issn = | pmid = 20965969|doi = 10.1093/nar/gkq945| bibcode = | oclc =| id = | url = | pmc = 3013796 | format = | accessdate = | laysummary = | laysource = | laydate = | quote = }}</ref> The database describes a total of 529 (potential) human transcription co-factors interacting with a total of 1365 human transcription factors.
